{
  "bindingId": "project-binding.phosphene",
  "userAuthoredOraclePolicyText": "For every requirement class, expected values must originate from the strongest binding-required oracle that is executable, mechanically extractable, or otherwise independently observable.\n\nAn executable reference adapter is mandatory whenever the governing authority or a faithful reference implementation can reasonably be built, run, instrumented, or observed with available tools.\n\nImplementation cost, inconvenience, task size, absence of an existing adapter, or producer preference does not make an oracle unavailable.\n\n`hand-derived-exact` is forbidden unless I separately authorize it for a specifically named requirement class after retained evidence demonstrates that every stronger required oracle is unavailable.\n\nAuthority priority and oracle availability are different:\n\n* Stronger authority determines the behavior that PHOSPHENE must reproduce.\n* A lower-tier executable implementation may provide measurements but may not silently override stronger authority.\n* Any disagreement must produce an explicit authority-conflict record and remain FAIL until resolved.\n\nPreserve this section verbatim as the user-authored source for the binding's oracle-precedence policy.",
  "userAuthoredInventoryPolicyText": "Mechanically enumerate every behavior that can be enumerated from:\n\n* accepted source formats;\n* authoritative source and documentation;\n* retained binaries and libraries;\n* shaders;\n* node and port definitions;\n* parsed fields and defaults;\n* expressions and random behavior;\n* audio and timing systems;\n* execution paths and pass order;\n* state and persistence lifecycles;\n* render resources and pipeline state;\n* retained corpora.\n\nAssign every behavior a stable inventory ID.\n\nEvery inventory ID must map to sufficient:\n\n* claims;\n* exact authority identity;\n* strongest-required oracle evidence;\n* discriminating fixtures;\n* plausible-alternative evaluators;\n* comparators;\n* actual PHOSPHENE executor paths;\n* positive controls;\n* negative controls.\n\nCombining behaviors into a coarse claim may not reduce the evidence, fixture, alternative, execution, or coverage obligation for any individual behavior.\n\nThe retained corpus exercises scope but does not define completeness.\n\nPreserve this section verbatim as the user-authored source for the binding's inventory procedures.",
  "repository": {
    "repositoryId": "Stuff-is-Parts/sip-phosphene",
    "canonicalRemote": "https://github.com/Stuff-is-Parts/sip-phosphene"
  },
